## 7. Module 03 — Risk Engine

> **File:** [modules/03_risk_engine/scorer.py](file:///d:/Final%20Project/MASTER%20QA%20AGENT/modules/03_risk_engine/scorer.py) — 124 lines

**Class:** [RiskScorer](file:///d:/Final%20Project/MASTER%20QA%20AGENT/modules/03_risk_engine/scorer.py#6-115)

### Algorithm

The risk score combines three weighted factors:

```
risk_score = base_score + (historical_failure_rate × 0.3) + (ml_failure_probability × 0.7)
```

| Factor | Source | Weight |
|--------|--------|--------|
| `base_score` | Priority (HIGH=0.8, MEDIUM=0.5, LOW=0.2) | Base |
| `historical_failure_rate` | Real pass/fail ratio from ALL `*_results.json` files | 30% |
| `ml_failure_probability` | Module 10 Random Forest prediction | 70% |

### Risk Classification

| Risk Score | Level | Execution Order |
|-----------|-------|-----------------|
| ≥ 0.8 | CRITICAL | 1 (runs first) |
| ≥ 0.5 | MODERATE | 2 |
| < 0.5 | LOW | 3 (runs last) |

**Key Functions:**

| Function | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| [_build_historical_failure_map()](file:///d:/Final%20Project/MASTER%20QA%20AGENT/modules/03_risk_engine/scorer.py#14-40) | Scans ALL result files, builds `{test_id: {passed: N, failed: N}}` |
| [_get_real_failure_rate(test_id)](file:///d:/Final%20Project/MASTER%20QA%20AGENT/modules/03_risk_engine/scorer.py#41-51) | Returns 0.0–1.0 failure rate; defaults to 0.10 for new tests |
| [score_and_prioritize(run_id)](file:///d:/Final%20Project/MASTER%20QA%20AGENT/modules/03_risk_engine/scorer.py#52-115) | Loads approved scenarios, scores, sorts, saves prioritized plan |

