## 8. Module 04 — Test Code Generator

> **File:** [modules/04_test_code_generator/cypress_builder.py](file:///d:/Final%20Project/MASTER%20QA%20AGENT/modules/04_test_code_generator/cypress_builder.py) — 340 lines

**Class:** [CypressBuilder](file:///d:/Final%20Project/MASTER%20QA%20AGENT/modules/04_test_code_generator/cypress_builder.py#7-330)

### Design

This is the **AST-like code builder** that programmatically generates valid [.cy.js](file:///d:/Final%20Project/MASTER%20QA%20AGENT/cypress/e2e/crawler.cy.js) Cypress spec files. It doesn't use string templates — it constructs JavaScript code through conditional Python logic.

### Test Type → Code Mapping

| Strategy in Scenario | Generated Cypress Code |
|---------------------|----------------------|
| `Fill all inputs -> Submit` | Fills email/password/number/tel/text fields, textareas, dropdowns → submits → checks readyState + success indicators |
| `Leave inputs blank -> Submit` | Submits empty form → verifies `.error`, `.invalid-feedback`, `:invalid` |
| `Inject SQLi/NoSQL` | Types `' OR 1=1; --` into all inputs → submits → asserts no "Internal Server Error" or "SQL" in body |
| `Click -> Wait for routing` | Clicks → verifies URL change or SPA content update |
| `Wait for DOM mutation` | Counts `$('*').length` before/after click → logs DOM element diff |
| `TC_A11Y` | Scans all `<img>` for alt text, all inputs for labels/aria-labels, checks `tabindex` |
| `TC_SELECT` | Selects second `<option>` → verifies `.should('have.value', ...)` |
| `TC_TEXTAREA` | Types multi-line + special chars → asserts non-empty value |

**Key Functions:**

| Function | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| [_escape_selector(selector)](file:///d:/Final%20Project/MASTER%20QA%20AGENT/modules/04_test_code_generator/cypress_builder.py#25-34) | Escapes backticks and `${}` for safe template literal usage |
| [_escape_describe_text(text)](file:///d:/Final%20Project/MASTER%20QA%20AGENT/modules/04_test_code_generator/cypress_builder.py#35-40) | Prevents syntax errors in [describe()](file:///d:/Final%20Project/MASTER%20QA%20AGENT/modules/04_test_code_generator/cypress_builder.py#35-40) / [it()](file:///d:/Final%20Project/MASTER%20QA%20AGENT/modules/02_scenario_generator/rule_engine.py#7-10) blocks |
| [_get_timeout_for_test(test_id, strategy)](file:///d:/Final%20Project/MASTER%20QA%20AGENT/modules/04_test_code_generator/cypress_builder.py#41-51) | Context-aware timeouts: forms=15s, nav=10s, a11y=8s, default=7s |
| [write_spec(scenario, filepath, run_id)](file:///d:/Final%20Project/MASTER%20QA%20AGENT/modules/04_test_code_generator/cypress_builder.py#52-301) | Generates one complete [.cy.js](file:///d:/Final%20Project/MASTER%20QA%20AGENT/cypress/e2e/crawler.cy.js) file |
| [build_test_suite(run_id)](file:///d:/Final%20Project/MASTER%20QA%20AGENT/modules/04_test_code_generator/cypress_builder.py#302-330) | Clears old specs, iterates prioritized plan, generates all specs |

### Self-Healing Integration

At construction time, the builder queries the [SelfHealer](file:///d:/Final%20Project/MASTER%20QA%20AGENT/modules/09_self_healing/healer.py#6-157) memory bank. If a fallback selector exists, it creates a **robust multi-selector**:

```javascript
const robustSelector = `original_selector, healed_fallback_selector`;
```

### Visual Regression Anchor

Every generated test ends with:
```javascript
cy.screenshot('{run_id}__{test_id}', { capture: 'viewport', overwrite: true });
```

