## 9. Module 05 — Cypress Executor

> **File:** [modules/05_executor/run_tests.py](file:///d:/Final%20Project/MASTER%20QA%20AGENT/modules/05_executor/run_tests.py) — 219 lines

**Class:** [CypressExecutor](file:///d:/Final%20Project/MASTER%20QA%20AGENT/modules/05_executor/run_tests.py#8-210)

### Design

Implements a **batched execution engine** with a **self-healing retry loop**.

### Execution Flow

```
1. Load prioritized execution plan
2. Map spec files to scenario metadata
3. FOR attempt = 1 to 3 (max_retries):
   a. Clean up old status JSON files
   b. Join all pending specs into comma-separated --spec arg
   c. Run: npx cypress run --spec "spec1.js,spec2.js,..."
   d. FOR each spec:
      - Read {spec}_status.json (written by cypress.config.js after:spec hook)
      - If passed on attempt > 1 → mark as FLAKY
      - If failed AND not SYNTAX_ERROR → trigger Self-Healer → rewrite spec → add to retry list
4. Compile final results JSON
```

### Smart Retry Logic

| Condition | Action |
|-----------|--------|
| Failed + duration=0 + SYNTAX_ERROR | **Skip retry** (code gen crash won't fix itself) |
| Failed + has selector | Trigger `SelfHealer.register_failure()` → regenerate spec → retry |
| Passed on attempt > 1 | Mark `flaky: true` |

### Output Contract

Writes `results/{run_id}_results.json`:
```json
{
  "run_id": "run_20260304_162750",
  "target_url": "https://example.com",
  "timestamp": "2026-03-04T16:27:50",
  "tests": [{ "test_id", "status", "flaky", "attempts", "execution_time_ms", "error_message", "error_type" }],
  "summary": { "total", "passed", "failed", "execution_time_sec", "status" }
}
```

