## 10. Module 06 — Flakiness Detector

> **File:** [modules/06_flakiness_detector/flakiness.py](file:///d:/Final%20Project/MASTER%20QA%20AGENT/modules/06_flakiness_detector/flakiness.py) — 91 lines

**Class:** [FlakinessDetector](file:///d:/Final%20Project/MASTER%20QA%20AGENT/modules/06_flakiness_detector/flakiness.py#7-87)

### Algorithm

**Flip-Rate Flakiness Score:**

```
flakiness_score = number_of_state_flips / (total_runs - 1)
```

- A test is **flaky** if it has both passed AND failed across historical runs
- Score of **1.0** = perfectly flaky (alternates pass/fail every run)
- Score of **0.0** = perfectly stable
- Requires minimum **3 historical runs** to activate

| Function | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| [_get_all_historical_results()](file:///d:/Final%20Project/MASTER%20QA%20AGENT/modules/06_flakiness_detector/flakiness.py#16-26) | Loads all `*_results.json` sorted oldest→newest |
| [calculate_flakiness()](file:///d:/Final%20Project/MASTER%20QA%20AGENT/modules/06_flakiness_detector/flakiness.py#27-87) | Computes flip-rate per test_id, saves [flakiness_report.json](file:///d:/Final%20Project/MASTER%20QA%20AGENT/results/flakiness_report.json) |

