## 11. Module 07 — API Anomaly Detector

> **File:** [modules/07_api_anomaly_detector/anomaly.py](file:///d:/Final%20Project/MASTER%20QA%20AGENT/modules/07_api_anomaly_detector/anomaly.py) — 155 lines

**Class:** [APIAnomalyDetector](file:///d:/Final%20Project/MASTER%20QA%20AGENT/modules/07_api_anomaly_detector/anomaly.py#6-145)

### Algorithm — Statistical Z-Score Analysis

Computes **mean** and **standard deviation** of execution times per module across ALL historical runs, then flags current-run tests that deviate.

### 4 Anomaly Types

| Type | Detection Logic |
|------|----------------|
| **Execution Time Spike** | Z-score > 2.0 above historical mean for the module |
| **Zero-Duration Failure** | `duration == 0` AND `status == failed` → crash/syntax error |
| **Multi-Retry Failure** | `attempts >= 2` AND `status == failed` → persistent instability |
| **Flaky Recovery** | `attempts >= 2` AND `status == passed` → intermittent issue |

**Key Functions:**

| Function | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| [_compute_historical_baseline()](file:///d:/Final%20Project/MASTER%20QA%20AGENT/modules/07_api_anomaly_detector/anomaly.py#17-46) | Builds `{module: {mean, std_dev}}` from all results |
| [analyze_api_responses(run_id)](file:///d:/Final%20Project/MASTER%20QA%20AGENT/modules/07_api_anomaly_detector/anomaly.py#47-145) | Runs 4-type anomaly detection, saves `{run_id}_anomalies.json` |

---

## 12. Module 08 — Visual Regression

> **File:** [modules/08_visual_regression/comparator.py](file:///d:/Final%20Project/MASTER%20QA%20AGENT/modules/08_visual_regression/comparator.py) — 136 lines

**Class:** [VisualComparator](file:///d:/Final%20Project/MASTER%20QA%20AGENT/modules/08_visual_regression/comparator.py#10-128)

### Computer Vision Pipeline

Uses **OpenCV** and **scikit-image SSIM** for pixel-level UI comparison.

```
1. Glob all .png screenshots from cypress/screenshots/
2. Map each to a canonical test_id (handle both anchored and failed screenshots)
3. If no baseline exists → set current as baseline
4. If baseline exists:
   a. Resize to match dimensions
   b. Convert to grayscale
   c. Compute SSIM (Structural Similarity Index)
   d. If SSIM < 0.999 → threshold → find contours → draw RED bounding boxes → save diff heatmap
```

### Key Libraries Used

| Library | Function | Purpose |
|---------|----------|---------|
| `cv2.imread` | Load images | Read baseline & current screenshots |
| `cv2.cvtColor` | Color conversion | BGR → Grayscale for comparison |
| `cv2.resize` | Dimension normalization | Handle viewport size differences |
| `cv2.threshold` | Binary thresholding | Create diff mask with Otsu's method |
| `cv2.findContours` | Contour detection | Identify changed regions |
| `cv2.rectangle` | Bounding boxes | Draw RED rectangles over changes |
| `ssim()` | Structural Similarity | 0.0–1.0 similarity score |

### Threshold

- **< 0.999 SSIM** = Visual anomaly detected (extremely strict — catches even minor pixel shifts)
- Contours smaller than 5×5 pixels are filtered as noise

---

## 13. Module 09 — Self-Healing Engine

> **File:** [modules/09_self_healing/healer.py](file:///d:/Final%20Project/MASTER%20QA%20AGENT/modules/09_self_healing/healer.py) — 158 lines

**Class:** [SelfHealer](file:///d:/Final%20Project/MASTER%20QA%20AGENT/modules/09_self_healing/healer.py#6-157)

### 4-Strategy Healing Cascade

When a selector fails, the healer tries four strategies in order:

| Strategy | Name | Logic | Example |
|----------|------|-------|---------|
| **1** | DOM Snapshot Lookup | Searches crawled DOM for alternative visible elements of same tag type | `form[name='search']` |
| **2** | Attribute-Based Fallback | If original used `.class` or `#id`, tries `[name]`, `[data-testid]`, `[aria-label]` | `form[name], form[data-testid]` |
| **3** | Tag + Visibility Fallback | Uses `:visible:first` pseudo-selector | `button:visible:first` |
| **4** | Generic Last Resort | Matches any visible element | `*:visible:first` |

### Memory Bank

All learned fallbacks are persisted to [data/healed_selectors.json](file:///d:/Final%20Project/MASTER%20QA%20AGENT/data/healed_selectors.json):
```json
{
  "form#old-id.old-class": {
    "fallback": "form[name='search']",
    "strategy": "dom_lookup",
    "healed": true
  }
}
```

**Key Functions:**

| Function | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| [get_fallback(selector)](file:///d:/Final%20Project/MASTER%20QA%20AGENT/modules/09_self_healing/healer.py#16-27) | Query memory bank for known healing |
| [register_failure(selector, test_id, run_id)](file:///d:/Final%20Project/MASTER%20QA%20AGENT/modules/09_self_healing/healer.py#80-132) | Execute 4-strategy cascade, persist result |
| [_search_dom_snapshot(selector, run_id)](file:///d:/Final%20Project/MASTER%20QA%20AGENT/modules/09_self_healing/healer.py#34-79) | Strategy 1: cross-reference DOM JSON files |
| [_extract_tag_from_selector(selector)](file:///d:/Final%20Project/MASTER%20QA%20AGENT/modules/09_self_healing/healer.py#28-33) | Regex extract base tag name |
| [get_healing_summary()](file:///d:/Final%20Project/MASTER%20QA%20AGENT/modules/09_self_healing/healer.py#149-157) | Returns all healings for dashboard display |

