## 14. Module 10 — CI Failure Predictor

> **File:** [modules/10_ci_predictor/predictor.py](file:///d:/Final%20Project/MASTER%20QA%20AGENT/modules/10_ci_predictor/predictor.py) — 80 lines

**Class:** [FailurePredictor](file:///d:/Final%20Project/MASTER%20QA%20AGENT/modules/10_ci_predictor/predictor.py#7-80)

### ML Algorithm: Random Forest Classifier

| Aspect | Detail |
|--------|--------|
| **Algorithm** | `sklearn.ensemble.RandomForestClassifier` |
| **Estimators** | 10 trees |
| **Training Data** | ALL historical `*_results.json` test outcomes |
| **Minimum Training Size** | 10+ samples with at least 1 failure |
| **Output** | `failure_probability` (0.0 to 1.0) per scenario |

### Feature Vector (4 dimensions)

| Feature | Extraction Logic |
|---------|-----------------|
| `priority_score` | HIGH=3, MEDIUM=2, LOW=1 |
| `selector_complexity` | `len(selector_used)` — longer selectors are more fragile |
| `is_form` | 1 if "form" in selector, else 0 |
| `has_interaction` | 1 if "mutation" in strategy, else 0 |

### Fallback Heuristic

If `scikit-learn` is unavailable or training data is sparse:
```python
base_prob = 0.15 if is_form else 0.02
base_prob += selector_complexity * 0.001
```

