## 22. Use Cases for Automation Testers

### 1. Rapid Test Suite Bootstrap
**Scenario:** QA team receives a new web application.
**Action:** Point the agent at any URL → get 30-70 Cypress tests in minutes.
**Value:** Eliminates weeks of manual test script writing.

### 2. Regression Testing After UI Changes
**Scenario:** Developer changes CSS classes or element IDs.
**Action:** Self-healer detects broken selectors → learns fallback → retries automatically.
**Value:** Zero manual maintenance when UI code changes.

### 3. Security Vulnerability Scanning
**Scenario:** Need to verify SQL injection protection.
**Action:** Every detected form gets a `TC_FORM_NEG_*_MALFORMED` test injecting `' OR 1=1; --`.
**Value:** Automated security audit of all input surfaces.

### 4. Accessibility Compliance
**Scenario:** Must verify WCAG compliance.
**Action:** `TC_A11Y` tests check alt text, aria-labels, keyboard focusability.
**Value:** Automated accessibility scanning on every run.

### 5. Multi-Site Benchmarking
**Scenario:** Compare quality across staging/production or multiple microservices.
**Action:** `--urls` mode crawls all sites → Swarm Comparison tab shows reliability matrix.
**Value:** Executive-level quality visibility across the entire portfolio.

### 6. CI/CD Gate
**Scenario:** Block deployments with failing tests.
**Action:** GitHub Actions runs nightly → GO/NO-GO recommendation.
**Value:** Zero-configuration quality gate in the deployment pipeline.

### 7. Visual Regression During Redesigns
**Scenario:** Track unintended UI changes during a redesign.
**Action:** Screenshots compared with 99.9% SSIM threshold → red bounding boxes highlight differences.
**Value:** Pixel-perfect visual quality assurance.

### 8. Flakiness Root Cause Investigation
**Scenario:** Tests pass/fail randomly, eroding team trust.
**Action:** Flakiness detector computes flip-rate scores → Root Cause Analyzer shows real Cypress errors.
**Value:** Targeted debugging instead of guessing.

