## 25.  Data Retention Policy — Implemented
3 Files Changed
File	Change

agent/cleanup_old_runs.py
NEW — Full garbage collector with time + count limits

config/agent_config.json
Added data_retention section with configurable limits

agent/agent_runner.py
Wired cleanup as STEP 7 at the end of both single-URL and multi-URL pipelines
How It Now Works
The pipeline now has a 7th step that runs automatically at the end of every successful execution:

STEP 1: DOM Crawler → STEP 2: Scenarios → STEP 3: Risk → STEP 4: Code Gen
→ STEP 5: Executor → STEP 6: Analytics → STEP 7: 🗑️ Garbage Collector (NEW)
Two Independent Limits
Limit	Default	What It Does
Time-Based	30 days	Any run_* files older than 30 days are deleted
Count-Based	50 runs	If you have 51+ runs, the oldest ones are purged
A run is deleted if it violates either limit.

What Gets Cleaned vs Protected
✅ Cleaned	❌ Never Touched
data/run_* (DOM, scenarios, approved, prioritized)	

data/healed_selectors.json
 (healing memory)
results/run_* (results, anomalies, visual regression)	data/screenshots/baseline/* (visual golden masters)
cypress/screenshots/run_* (execution screenshots)	

results/flakiness_report.json
 (regenerated each run)
data/screenshots/diffs/run_* (old diff heatmaps)	

config/agent_config.json
 (your settings)
Configurable in 

agent_config.json
json
"data_retention": {
    "retention_days": 30,
    "max_runs": 50,
    "enable_auto_cleanup": true   // set to false to disable
}
Can Also Run Standalone with Dry-Run


